---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy — Books"
  description="What books.oriz.in collects, what it doesn't, and your rights."
>
  <div class="spine-prose">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">
        <a href="/">CATALOGUE</a> / <a href="/legal/">LEGAL</a> / PRIVACY
      </p>
      <h1>Privacy policy.</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated · {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <h2>Who runs this</h2>
      <p>
        books.oriz.in is operated by Chirag Singhal, based in Bhubaneswar,
        Odisha, India, as part of the
        <a href="https://oriz.in/">oriz</a> family. Contact:
        <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — aggregate page views and
          country. Cookieless. No personal identifiers.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Authentication</strong> — if you sign in, Firebase
          Authentication stores your email, display name, and profile photo
          (if you sign in with Google/GitHub). We never see your password.
          The same login works across every <code>*.oriz.in</code> site.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Bookmarks</strong> — when you bookmark a book while signed
          in, the list of <code>bookCode</code>s is stored in Firestore under
          your user ID and accessible only to you.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact form</strong> — submissions go through Web3Forms
          which forwards them to my email. Web3Forms keeps copies; see their
          privacy policy.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Display ads</strong> — once approved, Google AdSense may
          set cookies to personalise ads. You can opt out via the consent
          banner or at
          <a href="https://adssettings.google.com">adssettings.google.com</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What we don't do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No tracking across sessions for analytics (Cloudflare is anonymous).</li>
        <li>No selling of personal data to third parties.</li>
        <li>No newsletters unless you explicitly subscribe.</li>
        <li>No PDF interception — chapter and full-book downloads go directly from your browser to <code>ncert.nic.in</code>; we never see them.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        You can delete your account from the
        <a href="/account/">account page</a>; this removes your Firebase Auth
        record and the Firestore documents under it (including bookmarks).
      </p>
      <p>
        Under India's DPDP Act 2023, you have the right to access, correct,
        and delete your personal data. Contact the
        <a href="/legal/grievance/">grievance officer</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        Books indexes school textbooks but is not directed at children under
        13. If you believe a child has provided data to us, contact the
        grievance officer for removal.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We will update this page when the practice changes, with the new
        date at the top. Material changes get a banner on the site.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
